TYPES:
Personal Area Network (PAN)
 -bluethooth
 -made of wireless modem, a computer or two, phones, printers, tablets, etc.,
 -revolves around one person in one building.

Local Area Network (LAN)
 -short distances
 -school, laboratory, university campus or office building
 -(within a building or between a group of two or three buildings in close proximity to each other)
 -Wireless Local Area Network (WLAN)

Metropolitan Area Network (MAN)
 -city(kangayam,karur)
 -large company
 -larger than LANs but smaller than WANs
 -entire geographic area (typically a town or city, but sometimes a campus).

Wide Area Network (WAN)
 -state/country
 -longer physical distances
 -connecting all computers together around the world
Campus Area Network (CAN)

Storage-Area Network (SAN)
 -connects shared pools of storage devices to several servers,
 -these types of networks don’t rely on a LAN or WAN

System-Area Network (also known as SAN)
 -new within the past two decades
 -provide high-speed connection in server-to-server applications (cluster environments),
 -storage area networks (called “SANs” as well) and processor-to-processor applications


LAN:
Ethernet:
 -standard way to connect computers on a network over a wired connection.
 -multiple devices, such computers, routers, and switches.
Token ring:
 -uses a special three-byte frame called a token
 -Only a host that holds a token can send data,
 -and tokens are released when receipt of the data is confirmed
